__pycache__/
*.pyc
*:Zone.Identifier

# pipeline/data/<site_id>/live/ (per-capture wind data + splash points) is
# tracked as of 2026-07-18 -- needed to persist across GitHub Actions runs
# (ephemeral runners, nothing survives between scheduled runs unless it's in
# the repo) and so the History view has real capture history to show, not
# just whatever's on one machine. Repo will grow steadily; the plan is to
# expire/archive older captures (e.g. to S3) later, not yet built.
#
# Still excluded: raw satellite PNGs (redundant with the published _web.jpg
# versions, large, only useful for future reprocessing) and the Herbie/GRIB2
# historical-archive pulls (pull_historical.py, made multi-site 2026-07-18 --
# path changed from the old flat pipeline/data/raw/ to per-site
# pipeline/data/<site_id>/raw/, hence the glob). Regeneratable raw
# intermediates either way; what matters is the *simulated* actual/forecast
# points published into site/data/, not this raw GRIB2-derived cache.
pipeline/data/maps_raw/
pipeline/data/raw/
pipeline/data/*/raw/

# Raw real-flight telemetry (GPS trackers and GPS-less altimeter exports
# alike, used for real-flight-vs-prediction analysis, see
# pipeline/analyze_real_flight.py) -- large, and potentially identifying of a
# specific flier/flight; only the derived summary (apogee, descent rates,
# landing coords, delta from predictions) gets published, never the raw logs.
pipeline/data/actuals/
